multiLocaleSummary.pt_BR:
Software architect, certified by Microsoft. With experience since 2005, working on Desktop, WEB and Mobile applications on the .Net platform;
Works in public and private companies of large, medium and small size, national and multinational;
Architecture, development and analysis of systems oriented to legal area, health, occupational medicine, commercial automation, process and rule automation, fleet management, civil construction, accounting, financial, billing, stock, advocacy, etc;
Modeling of processes / Functional and non-functional specifications / Architectural diagrams / Definition of software domains / Modeling of relational and non-relational databases / Adequacy and implementations / Application of concepts of Design Patterns, Integration of high complexity systems with Microservices, Agile Methodologies Scrum and XP;
ActiveMQ, RabbitMQ, Crossbar, Code Metrics with SonarQube, Golang, C#, T-SQL, ETL, TFS, GIT, Postgres, SQL Server, NoSql (Redis, MongoDb), SCRUM, SpecFlow, .Net Core, Net Framework, Windows, Linux, Firebase, GoF, Docker, Web API, Rest, Swagger, Hangfire, WindowsServices, ORM (EF e Dapper), Pub/Sub, Clean Code, SOLID, OO, DDD, BDD, TDD, CQRS, gRPC, IoC, DI, ElasticSearch, DevOps (CI/CD), Jenkins, Jmeter, xUnit, Websockets.

